          <p>Next table shows the forecast values for next five days and their
            probabilities -the most likely instance is adopted in the chart
            above. The model will generate a probability distribution for the
            index to be forecast and choose the most likely instance as its
            forecast value. The top 2 forecast values and there probability
            would be helpful. </p>
          <iframe width="700" height="200" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" src="/static/my_table_en.html"></iframe>
          <p><b>Note:</b></p>
          <ul>
            <li>The forecast value is actually a range around the number instead
              of a precise value. And the probability is the probability of the
              value falling into the range. Giving out a precise value is for simplicity
              and easiness to demo in chart！</li>
            <li>The probability is a result of the model's algorithm, not the
              probability of actual occurrence. It is more meaningful when compared
              to itself than considering the absolute value.</li>
